THE FALL OF RICHMOND, VA ON THE NIGHT OF APRIL 2ND 1865.
This strong hold and Capital City of the Davis Confederacy, was evacuated by the Rebels in consequence of the defeat at Five Forks of the Army of Northern Virginia under lice.
and capture of the South side Rail Road by the brave heroes of the North, commanded by Generals Grant, Sheridan and others. Before abandoning the City the Rebels set fire
to it, destroying a vast amount of property; and the conflagration continued until it was subdued by the Union troops on the following morning.
